From 9b7c5c05c580644effeecc7218f75e401f8d0c77 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Slick <slick@slicksync.local>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 19:05:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: file-based heartbeat diagnostics for activity monitor
 scheduler

Confirmed via a completely empty unfiltered docker logs dump over a
20-minute window (despite active traffic) that backend console
output isn't reliably reaching docker logs during steady-state
operation - same class of issue as v1.9.2's unconfirmed stdbuf fix.
Combined with hard DB evidence (WatchSession table 13+ hours stale
despite fresh upstream Nuvio checkpoint data confirmed present), this
means the scheduler's own logging can't be trusted to tell us whether
it's running at all.

Added file-based heartbeat logging (fs.appendFileSync, bypassing
stdout/stderr entirely - the same approach that successfully
diagnosed the Stremio Vault bug earlier) at every checkpoint: the
call site in index.js, scheduleActivityMonitor's init, checkAllAccounts
entry/error, and every stage of checkActivityForAccount (account
lookup, user lookup, before/after metrics processing, before/after
session processing, outer catch). Also brackets scheduleSyncs (the
one scheduler call not wrapped in try/catch) to test whether it's
silently blocking everything registered after it.

Bump to 1.9.30, changelog entry added.
